This past Friday, I had the privilege of visiting with asylum seekers in New York City. Giving back and being in service to the community fed my soul during this difficult time. I'm happy to say this is a positive post! I was so impressed and moved by the care and concern our city is showing these families. I live in New York. I believe in our great state. And I'm proud of what I witnessed. Our incredible public servants partner with community based orgs, faith based orgs and people who just care and want to be helpful to meet these migrants with dignity. It's an impossible task they've been dealt and yet everyday on average 600-700 people arrive seeking refuge, and these hardworking New Yorkers do what they can to keep them safe, fed and equipped to make their way in this country. To find solid footing and a better life. It is an unbelievable operation. Thank you @nycgov @nycemergencymanagement @nychealthsystem @zachiscol @newyorkcares @thisisabouthumanity among others.

#WelcomeWithDignity #ThisisAboutHumanity

(Photos by @ericapress.jpg)

During our visit, we were able to witness firsthand the services the city provides to these families and distributed 700 winter coats to every resident at the shelter for the upcoming weather. A wildly full circle moment for me! When my family immigrated to this country from Cuba, they were given coats through a federal program at the Freedom Tower in Miami before journeying to Connecticut for their first winter. I spent the morning talking to my mom about how she still remembers that moment and generosity. 

Thank you to @thisisabouthumanity for bringing community together in service of others and to the @nycemergencymanagement @zachiscol for coordinating the visit. These public servants are doing everything they can but the system is overrun and we need to take more steps to welcome people with dignity, to build more safe and humane immigration pathways, and to provide much more aid to cities like New York and others so they’re not left to burden this on their own. We all have a role to play, and that is why I encourage people to advocate for these policy changes and to follow @thisisabouthumanity, @immdef_lawcenter, and @fwdus to stay up-to-date on immigration policies and to learn about volunteer opportunities as they become available.

#WelcomeWithDignity #ThisisAboutHumanity

(Photos by @ericapress.jpg)

Okay one more shout out to the heroes. Thank you to the employees, volunteers and public servants who are on the ground facilitating this incredible operation. Everyone likes to talk about how complicated this issue is...these people make it very uncomplicated. They show up and they do the work. They look out for other people. Unbelievably inspiring and I can't wait to stand alongside them and do it again soon. 

#WelcomeWithDignity #ThisisAboutHumanity

(Photos by @ericapress.jpg)

Did you know homelessness in New York Public Schools has climbed to a record high? One in every 9 students lives in temporary housing and 1.4 million New Yorkers, including one in five children, are currently living in poverty. Help #NewYorkCares reach its goal of 200,000 coats this winter by collecting coats, organizing a drive or donating today. Link in the bio!

Grey’s Anatomy actress @itsjeaninemason and her husband, Nicholas, had one main objective for their New York City wedding: “How do we use this celebration to hire as many artists as possible?” 

From Brooklyn-based artist @mokshini creating custom illustrations to their neighbor, a Broadway violinist, performing during the ceremony, New Yorkers’ inherent creativity made their mission come to life effortlessly. 

See all the details of their stoop wedding (the same place he proposed) and restaurant reception at the link in bio. 🌆❤️
